1
00:01:31,410 --> 00:01:34,048
=The Glamorous Night=

2
00:01:35,208 --> 00:01:36,048
(Two years ago)
Judging from your resume,

3
00:01:36,048 --> 00:01:37,729
you have fairly extensive
work experience.

4
00:01:38,529 --> 00:01:39,568
But could you tell me

5
00:01:39,568 --> 00:01:43,009
why you left
your last company this March?

6
00:01:44,529 --> 00:01:45,328
I'd rather not say.

7
00:01:47,089 --> 00:01:50,328
Then can you talk about
your understanding of promotions?

8
00:01:52,568 --> 00:01:53,288
Promotions?

9
00:01:54,649 --> 00:01:55,889
Just promotions.

10
00:01:56,568 --> 00:01:59,568
So why did you apply
for this position at our company?

11
00:02:03,249 --> 00:02:04,009
The pay is good.

12
00:02:08,288 --> 00:02:11,128
Can you tell me
about your career plans and goals?

13
00:02:14,568 --> 00:02:15,369
I don't know.

14
00:02:30,209 --> 00:02:30,929
Wang Hao.

15
00:02:38,128 --> 00:02:39,240
You are Wang Hao, right?

16
00:02:40,008 --> 00:02:40,608
Yeah.

17
00:02:41,128 --> 00:02:42,049
Do you have time now?

18
00:02:43,288 --> 00:02:45,369
I do have time. What do you need?

19
00:02:46,008 --> 00:02:48,008
Come on, have a coffee with me.

20
00:02:54,728 --> 00:02:57,848
The coffee at this restaurant is
just average. I'm not interested in it.

21
00:02:58,688 --> 00:02:59,848
I think it's quite good.

22
00:03:03,128 --> 00:03:04,008
Just tell me,

23
00:03:04,408 --> 00:03:05,649
why invited me for coffee?

24
00:03:10,568 --> 00:03:12,489
I looked at the case you sent earlier.

25
00:03:13,209 --> 00:03:15,368
I liked it. So I asked you
to come for the interview.

26
00:03:16,209 --> 00:03:19,008
I meet you in person today.
I think you are good.

27
00:03:19,209 --> 00:03:20,369
Very genuine and honest.

28
00:03:21,489 --> 00:03:22,288
I like that.

29
00:03:23,769 --> 00:03:25,209
But during the interview just now,

30
00:03:25,209 --> 00:03:27,049
I said things you didn't want to hear.

31
00:03:28,568 --> 00:03:29,848
No goals?

32
00:03:31,049 --> 00:03:32,168
That's perfectly normal.

33
00:03:32,728 --> 00:03:33,809
I get confused too.

34
00:03:34,089 --> 00:03:35,529
Even now, sometimes I don't know

35
00:03:35,529 --> 00:03:36,728
what my goals really are.

36
00:03:37,888 --> 00:03:40,448
Life just comes in stages.

37
00:03:41,288 --> 00:03:43,168
You can find a job to do for now.

38
00:03:43,329 --> 00:03:45,408
Then, slowly, you can look
for what you really want.

39
00:03:46,128 --> 00:03:47,049
Look for a better one.

40
00:03:52,568 --> 00:03:54,168
It sounds like you're offering me a job?

41
00:03:56,329 --> 00:03:58,209
You can work with me
for a while to try it out.

42
00:04:00,489 --> 00:04:01,249
Okay.

43
00:04:01,728 --> 00:04:02,888
Then I'll give it a try.

44
00:04:04,568 --> 00:04:05,809
You might not last through it.

45
00:04:13,794 --> 00:04:20,520
(Twenty thousand. Unavoidable. Wang Hao)

46
00:04:21,201 --> 00:04:25,672
=Episode 20=
(Rich)

47
00:04:25,848 --> 00:04:27,129
Rich, come here.

48
00:04:27,129 --> 00:04:29,569
See what I brought you.

49
00:04:30,728 --> 00:04:33,009
Ham sausage. Do you want some?

50
00:04:33,529 --> 00:04:34,288
Can it eat this?

51
00:04:34,529 --> 00:04:35,449
Of course.

52
00:04:35,449 --> 00:04:36,248
I can feed it?

53
00:04:36,248 --> 00:04:37,048
Sure.

54
00:04:37,769 --> 00:04:38,928
Rich, say thank you to her.

55
00:04:39,608 --> 00:04:41,608
Here's ham sausage.

56
00:04:44,168 --> 00:04:45,569
Would you like to adopt Rich?

57
00:04:46,288 --> 00:04:47,048
Adopt?

58
00:04:48,368 --> 00:04:49,569
You don't want to keep it?

59
00:04:50,848 --> 00:04:52,329
It's not that I don't want to.

60
00:04:53,488 --> 00:04:54,889
My boyfriend is abroad year-round.

61
00:04:54,889 --> 00:04:56,288
I'm going to join him next month.

62
00:04:56,529 --> 00:04:57,848
So recently,

63
00:04:57,848 --> 00:04:59,728
I've been trying
to find a family to adopt it.

64
00:05:00,168 --> 00:05:01,608
I haven't found a suitable one yet.

65
00:05:02,009 --> 00:05:03,488
I really can't take it with me.

66
00:05:03,608 --> 00:05:04,329
So,

67
00:05:05,248 --> 00:05:06,329
if you could adopt it,

68
00:05:06,329 --> 00:05:07,529
that would be perfect.

69
00:05:11,808 --> 00:05:12,889
Rich,

70
00:05:15,009 --> 00:05:17,209
do you want to go home with me?

71
00:05:25,168 --> 00:05:26,288
I've never had a dog before,

72
00:05:27,048 --> 00:05:28,288
but I can try.

73
00:05:28,529 --> 00:05:29,449
I think you can do it.

74
00:05:30,248 --> 00:05:31,529
Greet your godmother, Rich.

75
00:05:31,969 --> 00:05:34,408
- Hurry, thank godmother.
- I am godmother now.

76
00:05:36,848 --> 00:05:37,928
No.

77
00:05:38,969 --> 00:05:39,969
Sorry about that.

78
00:05:40,889 --> 00:05:42,009
Rich.

79
00:05:42,009 --> 00:05:44,329
Shen Mo just bluntly told you

80
00:05:44,689 --> 00:05:46,769
he has heart disease
and asked you not to leave him?

81
00:05:47,569 --> 00:05:50,488
Right, straight to the point,
and very upfront.

82
00:05:51,168 --> 00:05:52,048
Upfront?

83
00:05:52,808 --> 00:05:53,649
He's shameless.

84
00:05:54,089 --> 00:05:55,649
He admits he's shameless.

85
00:05:56,889 --> 00:05:58,529
What kind of fate is this for me?

86
00:05:59,329 --> 00:06:00,848
I just divorced a gambler.

87
00:06:00,848 --> 00:06:02,488
Now here comes one with heart disease.

88
00:06:04,649 --> 00:06:05,848
Should I accept him or not?

89
00:06:07,329 --> 00:06:08,408
If I accept him,

90
00:06:08,408 --> 00:06:10,168
I'm afraid I'll be trapped.

91
00:06:10,168 --> 00:06:11,848
If I don't,

92
00:06:12,889 --> 00:06:14,889
I feel a bit sorry for him.

93
00:06:15,569 --> 00:06:17,009
You definitely shouldn't.

94
00:06:17,089 --> 00:06:19,168
How old is he? Fifty? Sixty?

95
00:06:20,569 --> 00:06:21,449
Fifty-three.

96
00:06:21,569 --> 00:06:22,969
He's fifty-three,

97
00:06:22,969 --> 00:06:25,048
while you're barely thirty.

98
00:06:25,848 --> 00:06:27,009
You should think it through.

99
00:06:27,089 --> 00:06:29,129
Will you serve an old man
for the rest of your life?

100
00:06:32,248 --> 00:06:33,168
I think you're right.

101
00:06:34,168 --> 00:06:35,449
I have my mom and kid.

102
00:06:35,449 --> 00:06:36,728
I can't take on another old man.

103
00:06:37,209 --> 00:06:39,089
Yes. I can't do that.

104
00:06:39,089 --> 00:06:40,048
Definitely not.

105
00:06:40,449 --> 00:06:42,449
You really need
to think more about yourself.

106
00:06:42,449 --> 00:06:43,209
Do you know that?

107
00:06:43,969 --> 00:06:45,608
I know.

108
00:06:46,889 --> 00:06:47,880
Take it out to go potty.

109
00:06:48,329 --> 00:06:48,829
Come on.

110
00:06:50,368 --> 00:06:50,969
Go potty now.

111
00:06:50,969 --> 00:06:52,969
I never expected you to have a dog.

112
00:06:54,288 --> 00:06:56,048
What about the dog
when you do night rounds?

113
00:06:57,089 --> 00:06:59,449
I just leave it at home
when I do night rounds.

114
00:06:59,848 --> 00:07:01,048
I installed a camera at home.

115
00:07:01,529 --> 00:07:03,009
If it's at home alone,

116
00:07:03,209 --> 00:07:04,168
I can check on it.

117
00:07:04,569 --> 00:07:05,480
It messes things up?

118
00:07:06,329 --> 00:07:07,408
It's very well-behaved.

119
00:07:07,949 --> 00:07:09,769
I feel like it has been trained before.

120
00:07:11,209 --> 00:07:12,488
How's that thing going for you?

121
00:07:13,009 --> 00:07:14,449
Has Barry calmed down?

122
00:07:16,129 --> 00:07:18,129
I'm not sure if he's still angry.

123
00:07:18,129 --> 00:07:19,608
He's probably doing better now.

124
00:07:20,329 --> 00:07:21,248
Barry loves

125
00:07:21,449 --> 00:07:24,728
showing off and building
his image through charity work.

126
00:07:25,129 --> 00:07:28,209
So I set up
a Responsible Drinking Week for him.

127
00:07:28,928 --> 00:07:30,088
I did it with media outlets,

128
00:07:30,689 --> 00:07:32,608
invited top influencers
from various industries,

129
00:07:32,608 --> 00:07:34,329
and made him ambassador.
He was thrilled.

130
00:07:34,889 --> 00:07:36,209
Foreigners always buy it.

131
00:07:37,449 --> 00:07:39,889
I also invited Shen Mo
as a distributor representative.

132
00:07:41,089 --> 00:07:41,689
Is he coming?

133
00:07:41,889 --> 00:07:43,168
Of course! It's a great chance.

134
00:07:43,168 --> 00:07:44,368
How could he miss it?

135
00:07:45,529 --> 00:07:48,368
He even took back
all the returned wine today.

136
00:07:49,408 --> 00:07:52,529
Smart move!
Killing two birds with one stone.

137
00:07:54,529 --> 00:07:55,649
All about people's will.

138
00:07:58,449 --> 00:08:01,089
But he's sick now,
so he probably can't make it.

139
00:08:03,089 --> 00:08:04,569
He'll likely send someone else.

140
00:08:07,906 --> 00:08:13,569
(Drink Moderately, Live a Happy Life)

141
00:08:13,569 --> 00:08:14,488
It's a bit crooked.

142
00:08:14,868 --> 00:08:15,368
Hello.

143
00:08:15,368 --> 00:08:17,538
(VIP Guest)

144
00:08:17,858 --> 00:08:19,348
(National Responsible Drinking Awareness
Week, Drink Moderately, Live a Happy Life)

145
00:08:19,348 --> 00:08:20,386
(Gustav Sapet China)

146
00:08:22,488 --> 00:08:24,488
Okay. First piece is
Crescent Moon Quartet,

147
00:08:24,488 --> 00:08:25,168
- right?
- Yes.

148
00:08:25,168 --> 00:08:26,449
Crescent Moon Quartet first.

149
00:08:26,449 --> 00:08:27,608
Then the second piece is

150
00:08:28,168 --> 00:08:28,889
- Minuet,
- Minuet.

151
00:08:28,889 --> 00:08:29,728
by Bach.

152
00:08:29,728 --> 00:08:30,449
Anything else?

153
00:08:30,728 --> 00:08:32,409
Beethoven's Ode to Joy.

154
00:08:32,409 --> 00:08:33,528
Beethoven's Ode to Joy.

155
00:08:33,848 --> 00:08:35,008
Keep the volume low.

156
00:08:35,008 --> 00:08:35,728
Keep it low.

157
00:08:35,728 --> 00:08:36,768
It mustn't overpower.

158
00:08:36,768 --> 00:08:38,089
Just keep it as background music.

159
00:08:38,089 --> 00:08:39,528
- Okay.
- Practiced already.

160
00:08:39,528 --> 00:08:40,289
Wang Hao.

161
00:08:43,209 --> 00:08:43,709
Ms. Zhao.

162
00:08:44,888 --> 00:08:46,648
The truss counterweights
are insufficient.

163
00:08:46,648 --> 00:08:47,728
With heavy winds today,

164
00:08:47,728 --> 00:08:49,809
what if the backdrop falls
and hits someone?

165
00:08:50,209 --> 00:08:51,400
Vendor's asking for scolding.

166
00:08:51,969 --> 00:08:53,049
Don't bother scolding them.

167
00:08:53,449 --> 00:08:55,848
Tell them to buy cigarettes
and give each worker a pack.

168
00:08:56,089 --> 00:08:56,648
Got it.

169
00:08:56,648 --> 00:08:57,409
Wait.

170
00:08:58,209 --> 00:08:59,449
Tell the vendor.

171
00:08:59,728 --> 00:09:01,209
If they won't even spend money

172
00:09:01,209 --> 00:09:02,209
on cigarettes,

173
00:09:02,209 --> 00:09:03,929
we won't spend money
on their final payment.

174
00:09:05,289 --> 00:09:06,089
Oh, right.

175
00:09:06,848 --> 00:09:09,329
Shen Mo's secretary called,
saying he's not coming tonight.

176
00:09:09,329 --> 00:09:10,689
He wouldn't say why when asked.

177
00:09:11,209 --> 00:09:13,089
I know why. Go ahead.

178
00:09:21,008 --> 00:09:24,049
- Grand and spectacular.
- It is just a small event.

179
00:09:24,848 --> 00:09:25,768
You are flattering me.

180
00:09:26,409 --> 00:09:27,768
I saw the guest list.

181
00:09:27,848 --> 00:09:29,888
What small event gets so many big shots?

182
00:09:30,449 --> 00:09:31,289
Well done.

183
00:09:31,329 --> 00:09:33,969
For charity,
everyone pitches in willingly.

184
00:09:33,969 --> 00:09:38,648
(National Responsible Drinking Awareness
Week, Drink Moderately, Live a Happy Life)

185
00:09:38,648 --> 00:09:40,008
Quite the scale today.

186
00:09:40,169 --> 00:09:42,329
Many company heads showed up.

187
00:09:42,648 --> 00:09:45,728
That's why I insisted you come,
both professionally and personally.

188
00:09:48,528 --> 00:09:49,648
Your wife is over there.

189
00:09:50,728 --> 00:09:52,169
If you don't need anything else,

190
00:09:52,169 --> 00:09:53,329
I'll attend to other matters.

191
00:09:53,969 --> 00:09:55,008
Wait, hold on.

192
00:09:57,569 --> 00:09:58,409
Here's the thing.

193
00:09:58,728 --> 00:09:59,528
I've been thinking.

194
00:09:59,528 --> 00:10:02,209
I was too harsh the other day.

195
00:10:03,329 --> 00:10:05,848
Sorry, please don't take it to heart.

196
00:10:06,089 --> 00:10:06,848
It's fine.

197
00:10:07,648 --> 00:10:08,409
I understand.

198
00:10:09,169 --> 00:10:11,169
You only snapped
because you were stressed.

199
00:10:11,329 --> 00:10:14,409
- If it were me, I'd be angry too.
- Thanks for understanding.

200
00:10:15,528 --> 00:10:16,488
I can understand

201
00:10:16,488 --> 00:10:19,008
why you said I'm not qualified
to be Sales Director.

202
00:10:20,128 --> 00:10:21,929
From the day I became a promoter,

203
00:10:22,008 --> 00:10:23,528
I never felt any boss

204
00:10:23,528 --> 00:10:25,528
was fully qualified to be my superior.

205
00:10:26,169 --> 00:10:27,368
Including Xu Yuntian.

206
00:10:28,008 --> 00:10:30,128
So I can understand you.

207
00:10:30,528 --> 00:10:31,768
That's arrogant.

208
00:10:33,768 --> 00:10:34,888
Aggressive spirit in sales.

209
00:10:37,888 --> 00:10:38,689
Mr. Fan.

210
00:10:40,488 --> 00:10:41,128
Zhao Mei.

211
00:10:42,768 --> 00:10:43,528
Long time no see.

212
00:10:43,528 --> 00:10:45,008
Long time no see.

213
00:10:45,169 --> 00:10:46,049
Let me introduce.

214
00:10:46,049 --> 00:10:48,648
This is Dong Yue.

215
00:10:49,528 --> 00:10:51,248
This is the CEO of Ruijin Consulting,

216
00:10:51,248 --> 00:10:51,888
Mr. Fan.

217
00:10:51,888 --> 00:10:52,528
Hello.

218
00:10:52,689 --> 00:10:53,768
Mr. Fan, nice to meet you.

219
00:10:54,608 --> 00:10:55,608
This is

220
00:10:57,289 --> 00:10:58,008
my husband.

221
00:10:59,008 --> 00:11:00,488
Mr. Li, long time no see.

222
00:11:01,928 --> 00:11:02,929
Have we met before?

223
00:11:03,929 --> 00:11:05,008
That event last time.

224
00:11:07,368 --> 00:11:09,409
Zhao Mei's event? I remember now.

225
00:11:13,049 --> 00:11:14,920
It's Barry. He is here.

226
00:11:16,328 --> 00:11:17,969
Mr. Fan, let's go greet him.

227
00:11:18,169 --> 00:11:18,669
Okay.

228
00:11:19,768 --> 00:11:20,409
Come along?

229
00:11:26,008 --> 00:11:28,209
Liming Group and Jingchu Group

230
00:11:28,449 --> 00:11:30,216
came because I begged
several major clients.

231
00:11:31,048 --> 00:11:32,289
Fan was going to Beijing

232
00:11:32,289 --> 00:11:35,248
to meet a crucial client today.
But I dragged him here.

233
00:11:38,008 --> 00:11:38,768
Barry.

234
00:11:47,608 --> 00:11:48,329
Barry.

235
00:11:49,528 --> 00:11:50,409
Let me introduce.

236
00:11:50,409 --> 00:11:52,368
This is Mr. Fan,
CEO of Ruijin Consulting.

237
00:11:52,768 --> 00:11:53,768
Hello.

238
00:11:54,128 --> 00:11:57,049
Thank you for strongly supporting
our Responsible Drinking campaign.

239
00:11:57,049 --> 00:11:59,648
- It's the least we could do.
- This is our head of HR, Ms. Qi.

240
00:11:59,648 --> 00:12:00,329
Mr. Fan, hello.

241
00:12:00,329 --> 00:12:01,049
Hello.

242
00:12:01,608 --> 00:12:02,248
This way.

243
00:12:03,289 --> 00:12:04,409
Actually, Dongming and I

244
00:12:04,409 --> 00:12:06,689
have always been your loyal users.

245
00:12:07,409 --> 00:12:08,008
Barry,

246
00:12:08,768 --> 00:12:11,728
the guests at today's event
are all heavyweight.

247
00:12:12,128 --> 00:12:13,969
It was all organized by my wife.

248
00:12:14,289 --> 00:12:14,929
By the way,

249
00:12:14,929 --> 00:12:16,689
I heard Shen Mo is also coming today.

250
00:12:16,888 --> 00:12:17,768
Very good.

251
00:12:21,528 --> 00:12:22,888
Please come this way for a photo.

252
00:12:25,008 --> 00:12:25,768
Barry,

253
00:12:26,049 --> 00:12:28,289
we'll go on stage to speak
in five minutes.

254
00:12:28,289 --> 00:12:29,329
Do you need to prepare?

255
00:12:30,528 --> 00:12:33,049
So soon? I'll quickly review it then.

256
00:12:37,089 --> 00:12:37,888
Drink moderately.

257
00:12:46,209 --> 00:12:46,929
Surprised?

258
00:12:48,689 --> 00:12:49,929
A bit. How come you're here?

259
00:12:50,409 --> 00:12:51,929
Because of your stupid event.

260
00:12:52,248 --> 00:12:53,608
I got up at 7:30 AM.

261
00:12:54,289 --> 00:12:55,569
What was your company thinking?

262
00:12:56,368 --> 00:12:59,528
A liquor company is
promoting responsible drinking?

263
00:12:59,689 --> 00:13:00,608
How hypocritical!

264
00:13:01,689 --> 00:13:02,368
I actually think

265
00:13:02,368 --> 00:13:04,409
if a liquor company
promotes responsible drinking,

266
00:13:04,409 --> 00:13:06,289
it will be more persuasive
and educational.

267
00:13:07,488 --> 00:13:09,008
That old man said the same thing.

268
00:13:09,368 --> 00:13:11,128
He's furious about you kicking him aside

269
00:13:11,128 --> 00:13:11,809
after using him,

270
00:13:11,809 --> 00:13:14,569
but he insisted I should come anyway,
saying it's a separate matter.

271
00:13:15,289 --> 00:13:16,969
What happened?
Why isn't Mr. Shen coming?

272
00:13:17,488 --> 00:13:18,089
He's sick.

273
00:13:18,788 --> 00:13:20,552
He said he wants me
to be VP at the company.

274
00:13:21,089 --> 00:13:22,289
If I perform well,

275
00:13:22,528 --> 00:13:24,248
he'll leave me more money in his will.

276
00:13:24,248 --> 00:13:25,409
What illness? Is it serious?

277
00:13:25,528 --> 00:13:27,400
Heart disease.
I don't know if it's serious.

278
00:13:27,848 --> 00:13:30,169
Anyway, he's got many bad habits.

279
00:13:30,169 --> 00:13:32,689
Him living this long
is already a miracle.

280
00:13:33,169 --> 00:13:34,929
Let's not talk about him.
Talk about you.

281
00:13:35,409 --> 00:13:38,329
Have you been secretly seeing
other women behind my back?

282
00:13:38,768 --> 00:13:39,488
I'm seeing.

283
00:13:40,008 --> 00:13:42,008
You're annoying!
Why do you always upset me?

284
00:13:43,569 --> 00:13:46,329
But no matter
how you upset me, I still like you.

285
00:13:46,569 --> 00:13:47,289
Stop this.

286
00:13:47,648 --> 00:13:48,449
Don't push.

287
00:13:48,569 --> 00:13:50,008
People are watching.

288
00:13:50,049 --> 00:13:51,848
We've broken up. Why are you doing this?

289
00:13:52,289 --> 00:13:53,409
But I didn't agree.

290
00:13:53,409 --> 00:13:54,728
You haven't told anyone, right?

291
00:13:55,049 --> 00:13:55,888
I didn't tell anyone

292
00:13:55,888 --> 00:13:56,888
because your dad told me

293
00:13:56,888 --> 00:13:58,008
not to say anything for now.

294
00:13:58,409 --> 00:13:59,008
Excuses.

295
00:13:59,608 --> 00:14:01,089
Is it him stopping you?

296
00:14:01,289 --> 00:14:02,888
Or are you afraid of losing his support

297
00:14:02,888 --> 00:14:04,008
and reluctant to say it?

298
00:14:05,608 --> 00:14:06,108
Both.

299
00:14:09,169 --> 00:14:11,209
Why do I like you so much?

300
00:14:14,689 --> 00:14:15,400
What is it?

301
00:14:16,768 --> 00:14:17,689
How wild!

302
00:14:19,128 --> 00:14:20,929
- What are you doing?
- I am kissing my boyfriend.

303
00:14:24,648 --> 00:14:25,648
What is that?

304
00:14:25,888 --> 00:14:26,768
We'll take our seats.

305
00:14:29,289 --> 00:14:30,969
It seems Shen Mo won't make it today.

306
00:14:31,648 --> 00:14:32,888
That's Shen Mo's daughter.

307
00:14:36,528 --> 00:14:39,049
It looks like she is pursuing that guy.

308
00:14:40,169 --> 00:14:41,409
Salesmen in this field

309
00:14:41,409 --> 00:14:43,169
all have some tricks
when dealing with women.

310
00:14:45,589 --> 00:14:48,209
Alright, next, let's welcome
with the warmest applause

311
00:14:48,289 --> 00:14:50,888
our advocate for responsible drinking
on this occasion,

312
00:14:50,888 --> 00:14:53,409
Barry, General Manager
of Gustav Sapet China,

313
00:14:53,409 --> 00:14:56,128
to come on stage
and deliver a speech for us.

314
00:14:56,128 --> 00:14:57,864
- My turn now.
- Please give him a round of applause.

315
00:15:04,072 --> 00:15:05,888
First, I want to thank you all

316
00:15:06,329 --> 00:15:09,648
for coming to our
Responsible Drinking event.

317
00:15:09,848 --> 00:15:10,969
As the Chinese often say,

318
00:15:11,488 --> 00:15:14,279
a gentleman needs to be
slightly drunk when drinking alcohol.

319
00:15:14,279 --> 00:15:17,809
True grace lies in knowing
when to advance or retreat.

320
00:15:18,449 --> 00:15:20,488
I'm very happy for this opportunity

321
00:15:21,008 --> 00:15:22,768
to meet all of you guys,

322
00:15:23,089 --> 00:15:24,128
my partners.

323
00:15:24,689 --> 00:15:27,368
I'm very thrilled
for the opportunity I have here.

324
00:15:27,528 --> 00:15:28,488
We all have here.

325
00:15:30,689 --> 00:15:32,449
I love you. I can't be without you.

326
00:15:33,728 --> 00:15:35,008
(When Shen Xing hugged me,)

327
00:15:35,008 --> 00:15:36,049
(I suddenly realized)

328
00:15:36,488 --> 00:15:39,008
(that although she's crazy,
she's actually not stupid at all.)

329
00:15:39,528 --> 00:15:41,728
(All her questions cut right
to the heart of the issue.)

330
00:15:42,128 --> 00:15:45,209
(For example, she knows
that on occasions like today,)

331
00:15:45,608 --> 00:15:47,329
(I would never let her
be too embarrassed.)

332
00:15:47,809 --> 00:15:50,608
(If even drinking requires rationality,
how could I not be rational?)

333
00:15:51,929 --> 00:15:53,449
This event is really good.

334
00:15:53,768 --> 00:15:56,648
I bet headquarters
will absolutely love this event.

335
00:15:59,008 --> 00:16:00,848
Zhao Mei is indeed a very smart person.

336
00:16:01,329 --> 00:16:02,728
She knows how to make me happy,

337
00:16:03,488 --> 00:16:05,648
although she spent
quite a bit this time.

338
00:16:08,768 --> 00:16:09,289
What's wrong?

339
00:16:09,888 --> 00:16:11,488
Internal Audit Department sent an email.

340
00:16:12,368 --> 00:16:14,409
It says one of our suppliers claimed

341
00:16:15,008 --> 00:16:16,848
that during their
internal investigation,

342
00:16:16,848 --> 00:16:20,409
they discovered their employee
bribed Zhao Mei.

343
00:16:20,608 --> 00:16:22,248
How much was the bribe?

344
00:16:22,969 --> 00:16:25,728
They attached an invoice
worth 20,000 yuan.

345
00:16:26,409 --> 00:16:27,569
It's from a pet store.

346
00:16:27,809 --> 00:16:28,608
A pet store?

347
00:16:29,409 --> 00:16:30,368
Are you kidding me?

348
00:16:33,442 --> 00:16:35,144
(Invoice Notification)

349
00:16:36,608 --> 00:16:38,768
When Tengyue Media's people
were doing internal review,

350
00:16:39,608 --> 00:16:41,929
they found this invoice worth
20,000 yuan from pet store.

351
00:16:42,648 --> 00:16:44,169
The reason they reported internally

352
00:16:44,888 --> 00:16:47,888
was that this asset
was given to you as a gift.

353
00:16:48,449 --> 00:16:50,008
Tengyue Media?

354
00:16:52,008 --> 00:16:54,528
The head of Tengyue Media and I

355
00:16:54,648 --> 00:16:57,768
only met once at a bidding meeting.

356
00:16:58,008 --> 00:16:59,929
I seldom talked to him.

357
00:17:01,008 --> 00:17:02,329
I don't even have his WeChat.

358
00:17:02,768 --> 00:17:04,409
How could I have accepted his gift?

359
00:17:04,409 --> 00:17:07,849
The person who contacted you
was Tengyue Media's Senior Manager,

360
00:17:08,369 --> 00:17:09,008
Lu Ting.

361
00:17:09,169 --> 00:17:09,929
Lu Ting?

362
00:17:12,248 --> 00:17:15,449
I don't know this person.
I have never heard of her.

363
00:17:17,609 --> 00:17:20,288
Call her over. I can confront her.

364
00:17:20,649 --> 00:17:22,649
She has already resigned.

365
00:17:24,889 --> 00:17:26,889
Then this is utterly ridiculous.

366
00:17:27,169 --> 00:17:28,929
You're questioning me based solely

367
00:17:28,929 --> 00:17:31,369
on notes left by someone

368
00:17:32,008 --> 00:17:33,808
who resigned and an invoice?

369
00:17:34,568 --> 00:17:35,969
And do you even know

370
00:17:35,969 --> 00:17:37,169
that Tengyue Media

371
00:17:37,169 --> 00:17:38,929
is no longer our supplier?

372
00:17:39,129 --> 00:17:40,768
Last week, during the bidding

373
00:17:40,768 --> 00:17:43,768
for the Spring Festival promotion,
they didn't win the bid.

374
00:17:43,889 --> 00:17:44,929
We are aware of that.

375
00:17:45,409 --> 00:17:48,169
However, they specifically informed us,

376
00:17:49,169 --> 00:17:51,449
so we have to look into it.

377
00:17:52,609 --> 00:17:53,129
Okay.

378
00:17:54,169 --> 00:17:55,209
Let me say this again.

379
00:17:56,369 --> 00:17:57,728
I do not know Lu Ting.

380
00:17:58,169 --> 00:18:00,528
I have not accepted anything

381
00:18:00,528 --> 00:18:03,369
from this person or this company.

382
00:18:03,768 --> 00:18:06,609
What you're asking me about now
is completely baseless.

383
00:18:07,288 --> 00:18:09,528
Then, have you received anything

384
00:18:09,528 --> 00:18:11,129
related to pets recently?

385
00:18:13,008 --> 00:18:13,768
Pets?

386
00:18:13,889 --> 00:18:15,048
A colleague saw

387
00:18:15,528 --> 00:18:18,689
you posted a dog
on Moments this morning.

388
00:18:23,088 --> 00:18:24,288
According to company policy,

389
00:18:24,689 --> 00:18:27,248
accepting assets worth more
than 5,000 yuan from suppliers

390
00:18:27,649 --> 00:18:28,768
is considered bribery.

391
00:18:31,048 --> 00:18:33,689
Zhao Mei, you must think
very carefully about this.

392
00:18:43,209 --> 00:18:44,689
(Zhao Mei)
(Hello, are you there?)

393
00:18:44,898 --> 00:18:49,520
(Message sent,
but rejected by the recipient)

394
00:18:50,088 --> 00:18:51,488
(My boyfriend is abroad year-round.)

395
00:18:51,488 --> 00:18:53,008
(I'm joining him next month.)

396
00:18:53,849 --> 00:18:55,008
(So recently,)

397
00:18:55,008 --> 00:18:56,768
(I've been trying
to find a family to adopt it.)

398
00:18:57,369 --> 00:18:58,969
(I haven't found a suitable one yet.)

399
00:19:00,129 --> 00:19:01,728
(I really can't take it with me.)

400
00:19:01,728 --> 00:19:04,209
(Lu Ting)
(So, if you could adopt him,)

401
00:19:04,209 --> 00:19:05,409
(that would be perfect.)

402
00:19:08,048 --> 00:19:08,568
Ms. Zhao.

403
00:19:12,649 --> 00:19:13,689
Do you know this person?

404
00:19:17,889 --> 00:19:19,248
I know her. She is Lu Ting.

405
00:19:19,689 --> 00:19:22,169
We worked together on events.
She's from Tengyue Media.

406
00:19:22,929 --> 00:19:24,409
But she probably resigned last month.

407
00:19:24,808 --> 00:19:26,369
Do you have her contact information?

408
00:19:26,369 --> 00:19:26,969
Yeah.

409
00:19:28,328 --> 00:19:29,409
What? Should I call her?

410
00:19:30,248 --> 00:19:30,768
Call her.

411
00:19:34,048 --> 00:19:36,528
The subscriber you dialed
cannot be connected.

412
00:19:36,689 --> 00:19:37,689
Please redial later.

413
00:19:37,689 --> 00:19:38,488
Strange.

414
00:19:39,889 --> 00:19:41,048
Let me send her a message.

415
00:19:46,889 --> 00:19:47,929
She blocked me.

416
00:19:52,409 --> 00:19:53,369
Expected.

417
00:19:54,568 --> 00:19:55,328
What happened?

418
00:19:56,248 --> 00:19:58,088
Before resigning, Lu Ting

419
00:19:58,088 --> 00:20:00,288
submitted an invoice worth
20,000 yuan to their company,

420
00:20:00,288 --> 00:20:01,488
saying she gave me something.

421
00:20:01,728 --> 00:20:04,649
So their company specifically informed
our internal audit team.

422
00:20:06,248 --> 00:20:07,048
I don't understand.

423
00:20:07,048 --> 00:20:08,169
They said I accepted a gift.

424
00:20:12,008 --> 00:20:12,808
Did you accept it?

425
00:20:12,808 --> 00:20:13,609
No!

426
00:20:19,008 --> 00:20:19,508
I did.

427
00:20:20,849 --> 00:20:23,008
But I genuinely didn't know
it was meant to frame me.

428
00:20:28,169 --> 00:20:29,328
I got set up.

429
00:20:30,169 --> 00:20:31,048
That wretch.

430
00:20:32,568 --> 00:20:33,568
What do we do now?

431
00:20:35,409 --> 00:20:37,449
Find Lu Ting
and return the thing to her.

432
00:20:37,768 --> 00:20:40,008
Then catch the mastermind behind this.

433
00:20:40,808 --> 00:20:41,568
Otherwise...

434
00:20:42,369 --> 00:20:43,288
Otherwise what?

435
00:20:46,808 --> 00:20:47,609
Otherwise...

436
00:20:51,248 --> 00:20:53,129
Do you know our company has a policy?

437
00:20:53,409 --> 00:20:55,048
Accepting gifts worth over 5,000 yuan

438
00:20:55,248 --> 00:20:57,288
from suppliers counts as bribery.

439
00:20:58,728 --> 00:20:59,808
I didn't know that.

440
00:21:00,008 --> 00:21:01,169
At worst,

441
00:21:01,369 --> 00:21:03,169
the company could fire me anytime now,

442
00:21:03,528 --> 00:21:05,288
without paying me any compensation.

443
00:21:06,088 --> 00:21:07,169
At best,

444
00:21:07,969 --> 00:21:09,169
this is a financial issue.

445
00:21:10,129 --> 00:21:11,889
They most likely won't promote me.

446
00:21:14,008 --> 00:21:16,528
I'll go find Lu Ting right now
and get to the bottom of this.

447
00:21:19,129 --> 00:21:20,409
Ms. Zhao, can I ask

448
00:21:20,409 --> 00:21:21,768
what you actually accepted?

449
00:21:30,008 --> 00:21:31,008
A dog.

450
00:21:34,449 --> 00:21:35,449
Shoot.

451
00:21:36,088 --> 00:21:36,588
Here.

452
00:21:43,929 --> 00:21:44,889
- Amazing.
- Here.

453
00:21:49,369 --> 00:21:50,248
Pet store invoice?

454
00:21:51,728 --> 00:21:52,449
For how much?

455
00:21:53,649 --> 00:21:54,288
20,000 yuan.

456
00:21:54,409 --> 00:21:55,209
20,000 yuan?

457
00:21:55,649 --> 00:21:57,889
For 20,000 yuan, the internal audit
team is investigating?

458
00:21:57,889 --> 00:21:59,649
Don't think 20,000 yuan
is a small amount.

459
00:21:59,649 --> 00:22:01,088
Many people have that misconception.

460
00:22:01,088 --> 00:22:03,112
Accepting gifts over 5,000 yuan
counts as bribery.

461
00:22:04,808 --> 00:22:07,088
So, you think Zhao Mei is innocent?

462
00:22:07,288 --> 00:22:08,808
I don't know if she's innocent or not.

463
00:22:08,808 --> 00:22:11,008
But from what I know,
she doesn't have a pet.

464
00:22:11,169 --> 00:22:13,568
She does! Didn't you see her posts?

465
00:22:14,129 --> 00:22:15,369
I seldom checked posts.

466
00:22:16,288 --> 00:22:17,889
It's already deleted.

467
00:22:18,649 --> 00:22:19,609
But I have it here.

468
00:22:20,288 --> 00:22:20,808
Look.

469
00:22:23,449 --> 00:22:25,929
Qi Youlan sent it to me
and asked for my handling opinion.

470
00:22:28,969 --> 00:22:30,048
So, what's your opinion?

471
00:22:31,288 --> 00:22:34,008
My opinion is simple.
Financial issue is a red line.

472
00:22:34,728 --> 00:22:37,488
Since the supplier reported it,
we definitely have to investigate.

473
00:22:37,889 --> 00:22:39,609
Because the amount isn't that large,

474
00:22:39,609 --> 00:22:41,409
we might not necessarily
ask her to resign.

475
00:22:41,728 --> 00:22:44,808
But she definitely won't get
the Sales Director position.

476
00:22:45,328 --> 00:22:47,129
So that's the real goal, right?

477
00:22:47,129 --> 00:22:48,129
To stop her promotion.

478
00:22:48,889 --> 00:22:49,889
It is obvious.

479
00:22:50,449 --> 00:22:52,969
But won't everyone think
I'm the one who set this up?

480
00:22:54,409 --> 00:22:55,528
Aren't you?

481
00:22:56,808 --> 00:22:57,449
(Moss Cafe)
Then this person

482
00:22:57,449 --> 00:22:59,328
knows your company's policies
way too well.

483
00:23:00,169 --> 00:23:00,889
Very familiar.

484
00:23:02,008 --> 00:23:03,768
Could it be someone from your company?

485
00:23:04,288 --> 00:23:05,008
Think about it.

486
00:23:05,409 --> 00:23:07,568
If Zhao Mei gets into trouble,

487
00:23:07,969 --> 00:23:09,929
who will benefit the most?

488
00:23:10,129 --> 00:23:12,689
Definitely Dong Yue. No need to think.

489
00:23:13,409 --> 00:23:14,728
Your promotion fails for bribery.

490
00:23:14,728 --> 00:23:17,248
He's the one who benefits the most.

491
00:23:17,649 --> 00:23:19,169
But I really don't think it's him.

492
00:23:19,568 --> 00:23:20,488
Back then, you thought

493
00:23:20,488 --> 00:23:23,008
Li Dongming was a good guy
rising above the filth.

494
00:23:26,048 --> 00:23:27,008
Think about it.

495
00:23:29,488 --> 00:23:30,808
So what are you going to do now?

496
00:23:32,048 --> 00:23:33,889
Do you want to be the hero
saving the damsel?

497
00:23:33,889 --> 00:23:35,808
Or throw stones while she's down?

498
00:23:38,088 --> 00:23:38,689
Both.

499
00:23:41,768 --> 00:23:44,008
Really, your imagination
is just too vivid.

500
00:23:48,008 --> 00:23:51,288
Do you think someone
might be trying to help you?

501
00:24:03,689 --> 00:24:04,808
(I heard about your issue.)

502
00:24:05,209 --> 00:24:07,609
(Dong Yue)
(Do you have a photo of the dog giver?)

503
00:24:08,248 --> 00:24:08,748
(Yes.)

504
00:24:14,690 --> 00:24:19,234
(Zhao Mei)

505
00:24:34,088 --> 00:24:34,689
Boss.

506
00:24:38,008 --> 00:24:39,889
Is your friend who helped
find the one I wanted

507
00:24:39,889 --> 00:24:40,849
last time still there?

508
00:24:42,008 --> 00:24:43,288
I need his help again.

509
00:24:44,488 --> 00:24:47,048
She should be easy to find.
She is in our circle too.

510
00:24:53,969 --> 00:24:54,528
Mr. Li.

511
00:24:56,689 --> 00:24:58,649
You guys go ahead. I...

512
00:24:59,409 --> 00:25:01,488
I left my phone at the restaurant.

513
00:25:01,488 --> 00:25:02,088
You go ahead.

514
00:25:21,969 --> 00:25:23,528
(Shan Yunfei)
(Did you see what she bought?)

515
00:25:28,409 --> 00:25:30,048
(Wang Xiaomi)
(She's drinking Brain Blast again.)

516
00:25:30,088 --> 00:25:31,808
(How many bottles has she had today?)

517
00:25:32,849 --> 00:25:34,328
(Shan Yunfei)
(She just bought many more.)

518
00:25:34,728 --> 00:25:36,889
(Chen Mina)
(It shouldn't be drunk too much, right?)

519
00:25:37,488 --> 00:25:39,008
(Wang Xiaomi)
(Too tired. No choice.)

520
00:25:39,008 --> 00:25:40,129
(She has to work overtime.)

521
00:25:41,288 --> 00:25:42,528
(Wang Anran)
(Who doesn't work overtime?)

522
00:25:43,649 --> 00:25:45,889
(Wang Xiaomi)
(It is nothing like ours.)

523
00:25:46,169 --> 00:25:47,328
(We do one kind of job.)

524
00:25:47,328 --> 00:25:48,008
(But her?)

525
00:25:48,008 --> 00:25:51,008
(She does one kind of job
during the day and another at night,)

526
00:25:51,008 --> 00:25:53,048
(Chatter Squad)
(and still works past midnight.)

527
00:25:55,568 --> 00:25:57,768
(Shan Yunfei)
(The 108 methods of working overtime.)

528
00:26:12,689 --> 00:26:14,209
Don't chat idly during work hours.

529
00:26:15,649 --> 00:26:17,728
Meeting in Conference Room 3
in ten minutes.

530
00:26:18,349 --> 00:26:19,349
- Yes.
- Okay.

531
00:26:25,969 --> 00:26:27,568
How does he know we're chatting?

532
00:26:28,288 --> 00:26:29,088
No idea.

533
00:26:29,169 --> 00:26:30,328
Any spyware on our computers?

534
00:26:32,169 --> 00:26:32,929
It can't be right.

535
00:26:33,409 --> 00:26:35,808
Why is Xiao so mean lately?

536
00:26:36,768 --> 00:26:38,609
The post-illness good days
ended that fast?

537
00:26:38,889 --> 00:26:39,689
He's anxious.

538
00:26:40,008 --> 00:26:41,488
The Shannan project

539
00:26:41,488 --> 00:26:43,328
got cut short
as the client ran out of money.

540
00:26:43,568 --> 00:26:45,369
The CVS project isn't still signed.

541
00:26:45,369 --> 00:26:46,768
Next year's KPIs

542
00:26:46,768 --> 00:26:48,008
won't be met.

543
00:26:50,248 --> 00:26:51,929
Does that mean more layoffs?

544
00:26:53,248 --> 00:26:53,889
Hard to tell.

545
00:26:54,649 --> 00:26:56,248
(Risk Prevention and Response Strategy)
Regarding the problems and challenges,

546
00:26:56,248 --> 00:26:57,568
we took countermeasures.

547
00:26:57,728 --> 00:27:00,488
Therefore, we must proactively
prevent potential risks

548
00:27:00,488 --> 00:27:02,008
and implement preventative measures.

549
00:27:02,248 --> 00:27:04,528
That concludes my summary. Thank you.

550
00:27:05,008 --> 00:27:05,609
Good.

551
00:27:08,568 --> 00:27:10,488
Next. Who's next, Xiaomi?

552
00:27:11,649 --> 00:27:13,369
Qiao Hailun, you're up.

553
00:27:24,728 --> 00:27:27,528
MT Company was not very satisfied
with the analysis and conclusions

554
00:27:27,528 --> 00:27:28,248
we provided

555
00:27:28,248 --> 00:27:29,248
(Contents)
in the last phase.

556
00:27:29,568 --> 00:27:31,689
The main issues are concentrated
in three areas.

557
00:27:32,209 --> 00:27:35,088
Competitor analysis,
response strategies, and team building.

558
00:27:38,929 --> 00:27:40,929
First, competitor analysis.

559
00:27:42,609 --> 00:27:43,209
Oh my!

560
00:27:43,209 --> 00:27:44,129
What is that sound?

561
00:27:44,129 --> 00:27:44,929
It's a cat meowing.

562
00:27:45,248 --> 00:27:46,409
It's in heat.

563
00:27:46,449 --> 00:27:47,849
Why that sound on her computer?

564
00:27:47,849 --> 00:27:49,008
What's going on?

565
00:27:49,008 --> 00:27:49,849
This is crazy.

566
00:27:49,849 --> 00:27:50,409
No, it's...

567
00:27:52,328 --> 00:27:53,248
Fix it, hurry!

568
00:27:53,248 --> 00:27:53,849
I...

569
00:27:55,288 --> 00:27:55,849
Well...

570
00:27:57,488 --> 00:27:58,609
How can you be so stupid?

571
00:27:59,488 --> 00:28:01,088
How did you even get hired with your IQ?

572
00:28:01,088 --> 00:28:02,449
I... Wait...

573
00:28:02,528 --> 00:28:03,609
Can you fix it or not?

574
00:28:05,008 --> 00:28:07,568
How long did MT Company give you
for the preliminary work?

575
00:28:07,969 --> 00:28:08,808
Still not satisfied?

576
00:28:09,328 --> 00:28:10,209
If you can't do it,

577
00:28:10,209 --> 00:28:11,328
let someone else handle it.

578
00:28:11,689 --> 00:28:12,768
Stop wasting time here.

579
00:28:13,088 --> 00:28:15,129
You're wasting
everyone's time in this room.

580
00:28:16,129 --> 00:28:16,629
I...

581
00:28:16,768 --> 00:28:17,728
Alright, enough.

582
00:28:19,768 --> 00:28:20,268
Xiaomi.

583
00:28:21,409 --> 00:28:22,088
You'll take over

584
00:28:22,768 --> 00:28:23,609
this project.

585
00:28:23,609 --> 00:28:24,129
Got it!

586
00:28:30,328 --> 00:28:31,248
Why are you waiting?

587
00:28:43,808 --> 00:28:46,088
To improve product quality and taste,

588
00:28:46,169 --> 00:28:49,409
MT Company continuously optimizes
its product formulations

589
00:28:49,409 --> 00:28:50,849
to meet consumer demands.

590
00:29:17,209 --> 00:29:19,568
I didn't know the woman
who gave me the dog

591
00:29:19,568 --> 00:29:20,288
is named Lu Ting.

592
00:29:21,488 --> 00:29:23,728
I always thought she was just
a regular running buddy.

593
00:29:24,849 --> 00:29:27,369
She said she was going abroad
and couldn't take the dog.

594
00:29:27,768 --> 00:29:29,008
She asked if I can keep it.

595
00:29:29,728 --> 00:29:30,568
I said yes.

596
00:29:32,088 --> 00:29:32,728
That's it.

597
00:29:33,008 --> 00:29:35,169
So you did accept that dog.

598
00:29:35,248 --> 00:29:37,568
I accepted it, but it wasn't a bribe.

599
00:29:37,568 --> 00:29:39,929
I was helping her take care of it,
do you understand?

600
00:29:40,609 --> 00:29:42,328
There's a fundamental difference here.

601
00:29:43,728 --> 00:29:45,169
I was set up.

602
00:29:45,169 --> 00:29:46,889
But you can't prove that.

603
00:29:47,048 --> 00:29:48,488
Based on the evidence we have,

604
00:29:48,488 --> 00:29:49,649
you did accept something

605
00:29:49,649 --> 00:29:51,129
worth 20,000 yuan.

606
00:29:51,649 --> 00:29:54,008
And it came directly from our supplier.

607
00:29:54,808 --> 00:29:56,409
I didn't know she was a supplier.

608
00:29:58,209 --> 00:30:00,129
What do I have to say
to make you believe me?

609
00:30:01,169 --> 00:30:04,248
I've worked at GST for ten years.

610
00:30:04,488 --> 00:30:05,209
I wouldn't

611
00:30:05,209 --> 00:30:06,728
stoop so low as to covet a dog, right?

612
00:30:06,728 --> 00:30:08,048
It's not like it's an apartment.

613
00:30:10,409 --> 00:30:11,768
Just kidding. Don't write it down.

614
00:30:12,488 --> 00:30:14,088
I was talking nonsense. Don't record it.

615
00:30:14,689 --> 00:30:15,328
Zhao Mei,

616
00:30:16,248 --> 00:30:16,808
stay calm.

617
00:30:17,528 --> 00:30:18,488
We're not enemies.

618
00:30:22,288 --> 00:30:23,008
No, I...

619
00:30:23,328 --> 00:30:23,969
I just

620
00:30:24,528 --> 00:30:27,169
truly feel like you're completely

621
00:30:27,169 --> 00:30:29,409
interrogating me as a suspect.

622
00:30:36,889 --> 00:30:37,389
Okay.

623
00:30:41,768 --> 00:30:42,808
Ms. Qi wants to see you.

624
00:30:51,010 --> 00:30:53,369
(Qi Youlan)

625
00:30:53,369 --> 00:30:54,169
Come in.

626
00:31:00,929 --> 00:31:01,528
Have a seat.

627
00:31:12,248 --> 00:31:14,969
Regarding the report filed against you,

628
00:31:15,568 --> 00:31:17,248
I've discussed it with higher-ups

629
00:31:18,008 --> 00:31:19,528
and gathered their input.

630
00:31:20,248 --> 00:31:20,849
First,

631
00:31:21,728 --> 00:31:24,129
you did violate company policy.

632
00:31:24,689 --> 00:31:27,649
But the amount involved was minor.

633
00:31:28,609 --> 00:31:29,488
Additionally,

634
00:31:30,008 --> 00:31:31,328
higher-ups highly values

635
00:31:31,409 --> 00:31:33,129
your contributions to the company.

636
00:31:33,689 --> 00:31:37,248
So we won't treat this as bribery.

637
00:31:38,768 --> 00:31:40,328
There's a 'but' coming, isn't there?

638
00:31:43,768 --> 00:31:46,969
But we can't proceed
with your promotion at this time.

639
00:31:54,048 --> 00:31:55,409
I don't accept this.

640
00:31:56,048 --> 00:31:57,649
I was framed.

641
00:31:58,288 --> 00:32:00,768
I refuse to accept it. Absolutely not!

642
00:32:06,209 --> 00:32:07,849
Seems Ms. Zhao's bribery accusation

643
00:32:07,849 --> 00:32:08,889
won't be cleared soon.

644
00:32:10,008 --> 00:32:10,728
What bribery?

645
00:32:11,528 --> 00:32:12,609
She didn't take bribes.

646
00:32:13,409 --> 00:32:14,609
I was just speculating.

647
00:32:14,609 --> 00:32:16,209
Everyone's saying it, right?

648
00:32:16,528 --> 00:32:17,528
The more people say it,

649
00:32:17,969 --> 00:32:19,048
the less you should say it.

650
00:32:20,449 --> 00:32:21,248
Hao,

651
00:32:21,929 --> 00:32:23,889
do you truly believe
she didn't accept that dog?

652
00:32:24,248 --> 00:32:24,849
No.

653
00:32:25,609 --> 00:32:27,088
Actually, I think she did take it.

654
00:32:27,328 --> 00:32:28,808
But she didn't view it as a bribe.

655
00:32:28,808 --> 00:32:31,304
She thought it was a dog
and never expected such consequences.

656
00:32:31,728 --> 00:32:32,649
What are you implying?

657
00:32:34,488 --> 00:32:35,849
I'm not implying anything.

658
00:32:35,849 --> 00:32:37,248
I'm just stating facts.

659
00:32:37,728 --> 00:32:38,568
Don't get defensive.

660
00:32:41,409 --> 00:32:45,929
Whether it's true or not, Ms. Zhao
has taken a major fall this time.

661
00:32:46,288 --> 00:32:48,488
And it's dragging
our whole department down.

662
00:32:49,488 --> 00:32:51,209
I heard internal audit team plans

663
00:32:51,209 --> 00:32:53,768
to investigate our department again.

664
00:32:53,768 --> 00:32:54,409
Really?

665
00:32:55,209 --> 00:32:55,849
That's brutal.

666
00:32:56,528 --> 00:32:58,768
When elephants fight,
the grass gets trampled.

667
00:32:59,568 --> 00:33:01,008
Enough. Just pipe down.

668
00:33:25,449 --> 00:33:27,288
Hey, Miss. All alone?

669
00:33:27,969 --> 00:33:28,768
Drowning yourself?

670
00:33:29,728 --> 00:33:30,369
Feeling upset?

671
00:33:31,929 --> 00:33:33,449
Drank too much? Let me take you home.

672
00:33:33,449 --> 00:33:35,449
Don't touch me!

673
00:33:35,449 --> 00:33:36,889
Do you even know where she lives?

674
00:33:38,209 --> 00:33:40,328
She's my girl. None of your business.

675
00:33:40,328 --> 00:33:41,449
And I'm your mother!

676
00:33:41,728 --> 00:33:42,449
What's her name?

677
00:33:43,808 --> 00:33:44,308
Get lost!

678
00:33:44,808 --> 00:33:46,088
Too young to be acting this way.

679
00:33:48,568 --> 00:33:49,568
Danning, you're here.

680
00:33:49,728 --> 00:33:51,488
How'd you get this messed up?

681
00:33:51,649 --> 00:33:53,248
Let's go home.

682
00:33:53,328 --> 00:33:54,248
Where to?

683
00:33:54,568 --> 00:33:55,528
Anywhere. Just move.

684
00:33:58,689 --> 00:34:00,048
Grab the wine.

685
00:34:00,048 --> 00:34:00,649
The wine.

686
00:34:03,248 --> 00:34:05,728
Black Knight?
Drinking the competitor's wine now?

687
00:34:08,929 --> 00:34:10,648
Check out this view.

688
00:34:12,568 --> 00:34:14,449
Paired with this excellent wine.

689
00:34:15,289 --> 00:34:16,648
This wine, let me tell you,

690
00:34:16,648 --> 00:34:18,688
I've always wanted to try it.

691
00:34:19,168 --> 00:34:20,729
It's exceptional.

692
00:34:24,249 --> 00:34:25,929
Let me taste it.

693
00:34:29,168 --> 00:34:32,249
Honestly, it's laughable.

694
00:34:34,528 --> 00:34:35,488
All because

695
00:34:36,289 --> 00:34:37,969
of a dog...

696
00:34:37,969 --> 00:34:40,008
I was ruined by a dog.

697
00:34:46,688 --> 00:34:48,128
I heard

698
00:34:48,929 --> 00:34:50,409
someone once said

699
00:34:51,329 --> 00:34:53,329
that in a company,

700
00:34:53,568 --> 00:34:56,289
if promotions came solely
through hard work,

701
00:34:56,769 --> 00:34:58,688
that company must be worthless.

702
00:35:01,088 --> 00:35:02,568
That was Li Dongming, right?

703
00:35:03,289 --> 00:35:03,929
Exactly.

704
00:35:08,449 --> 00:35:10,889
Today, I finally understand completely.

705
00:35:13,769 --> 00:35:15,409
I don't have that kind of luck.

706
00:35:16,008 --> 00:35:17,008
Don't talk nonsense.

707
00:35:17,008 --> 00:35:18,289
It's true.

708
00:35:18,528 --> 00:35:20,729
Really, the more I think about it,

709
00:35:20,729 --> 00:35:23,128
the more I feel
I'm not destined for this.

710
00:35:23,128 --> 00:35:26,048
What's the point of me trying so hard?

711
00:35:31,849 --> 00:35:33,128
I'm sorry, Danning.

712
00:35:34,809 --> 00:35:37,208
I must have disappointed you.

713
00:35:37,568 --> 00:35:39,008
What are you saying?

714
00:35:39,528 --> 00:35:40,889
Aren't we just employees?

715
00:35:40,889 --> 00:35:42,008
Is it really that serious?

716
00:35:42,289 --> 00:35:44,568
I'm deeply disappointed in myself.

717
00:35:45,088 --> 00:35:46,528
Just be happy.

718
00:35:46,528 --> 00:35:48,008
What's to be disappointed about?

719
00:36:04,322 --> 00:36:08,578
(Gustav Sapet China)

720
00:36:10,168 --> 00:36:11,048
I want to see Ms. Qi.

721
00:36:13,449 --> 00:36:14,528
Stop making a fuss.

722
00:36:16,048 --> 00:36:16,568
I admit it.

723
00:36:17,769 --> 00:36:19,369
You accepted reality so quickly?

724
00:36:21,369 --> 00:36:22,809
What else can I do?

725
00:36:23,648 --> 00:36:26,248
This whole thing is clearly a setup.

726
00:36:26,888 --> 00:36:28,969
The boss and my colleagues know it.

727
00:36:29,688 --> 00:36:31,048
But rules are rules.

728
00:36:31,488 --> 00:36:32,648
I did violate the rules.

729
00:36:33,289 --> 00:36:34,128
So I'll accept it.

730
00:36:35,168 --> 00:36:36,809
But you can also view this matter

731
00:36:36,809 --> 00:36:38,128
from a positive perspective.

732
00:36:39,369 --> 00:36:41,648
When someone climbs higher in status,

733
00:36:42,369 --> 00:36:44,568
they encounter absurd situations.

734
00:36:44,929 --> 00:36:46,849
Let me make an inappropriate analogy.

735
00:36:47,369 --> 00:36:50,008
Like when Xu Yuntian
encountered the sales lady,

736
00:36:50,008 --> 00:36:51,488
and you met that dog.

737
00:36:52,688 --> 00:36:54,688
It proves your life is on the rise.

738
00:36:55,168 --> 00:36:56,568
You're blocking someone's path.

739
00:36:56,568 --> 00:36:58,608
So they meticulously plot against you.

740
00:36:59,329 --> 00:37:03,488
Conversely, if you remained
at a very low level,

741
00:37:03,688 --> 00:37:06,208
who would target an ordinary sales lady?

742
00:37:06,969 --> 00:37:09,688
She'd never face such things, right?

743
00:37:12,409 --> 00:37:13,528
Thanks for comforting me.

744
00:37:26,809 --> 00:37:28,148
Okay, got it. Thanks.

745
00:37:30,289 --> 00:37:31,729
Does Wang Hao like you secretly?

746
00:37:33,849 --> 00:37:35,128
He told the internal audit team

747
00:37:35,528 --> 00:37:36,809
that the 20,000-yuan dog

748
00:37:36,809 --> 00:37:38,409
was a gift from Tengyue Media for him.

749
00:37:38,409 --> 00:37:40,568
He fostered it with you,
and you were unaware.

750
00:37:41,969 --> 00:37:42,608
What?

751
00:37:46,809 --> 00:37:48,008
I'll find him and stop him.

752
00:37:48,008 --> 00:37:48,809
Are you crazy?

753
00:37:49,369 --> 00:37:51,008
Wang Hao never accepted bribes.

754
00:37:51,008 --> 00:37:51,969
He's lying.

755
00:37:51,969 --> 00:37:53,008
He's saving you.

756
00:37:53,488 --> 00:37:54,128
Do I not know

757
00:37:54,128 --> 00:37:55,289
he's doing this for you?

758
00:37:55,289 --> 00:37:57,688
I've already confessed.
I don't need him to cover for me.

759
00:37:58,528 --> 00:38:00,249
Honestly, I shouldn't say this.

760
00:38:00,449 --> 00:38:01,969
But since I really can't find

761
00:38:01,969 --> 00:38:04,168
a better person than you
to lead the promoters,

762
00:38:04,889 --> 00:38:07,769
please accept Wang Hao's goodwill.

763
00:38:08,048 --> 00:38:09,008
What I can do is

764
00:38:09,008 --> 00:38:10,769
to ensure he leaves with full dignity.

765
00:38:11,208 --> 00:38:13,008
I won't accept his kindness.

766
00:38:13,289 --> 00:38:15,528
I refuse to let my people
take the fall for me.

767
00:38:25,008 --> 00:38:25,729
Where's Wang Hao?

768
00:38:26,729 --> 00:38:28,648
I haven't seen him. Did he come today?

769
00:38:28,889 --> 00:38:30,969
He hasn't replied to my morning text.

770
00:38:30,969 --> 00:38:32,409
Should I call him again?

771
00:38:40,889 --> 00:38:42,809
There's something else
I need to tell you.

772
00:38:43,008 --> 00:38:44,168
Fang said she's going home.

773
00:38:44,168 --> 00:38:45,048
- We're all persuading her. She...
- Wait.

774
00:38:45,048 --> 00:38:45,688
Wait a second.

775
00:38:56,162 --> 00:39:00,712
(Resignation Letter of Wang Hao)

776
00:39:11,810 --> 00:39:14,168
(Dong Yue is appointed
as Gustav Sapet China Sales Director)

777
00:39:14,168 --> 00:39:15,449
(Now Dong Yue is appointed)

778
00:39:15,648 --> 00:39:18,208
(as Gustav Sapet China Sales Director.)

779
00:39:23,648 --> 00:39:25,208
(I suddenly remembered a saying.)

780
00:39:26,128 --> 00:39:27,889
(Pure white expanse
that is utterly clean.)

781
00:39:29,048 --> 00:39:31,929
(After all that work,
I ended up where I started.)

782
00:39:33,568 --> 00:39:36,289
(Li Dongming said I need his help.)

783
00:39:36,929 --> 00:39:39,729
(Dong Yue said I'm unqualified
to be Sales Director.)

784
00:39:41,688 --> 00:39:42,729
(What they said)

785
00:39:44,369 --> 00:39:45,648
(makes perfect sense.)

786
00:39:57,362 --> 00:40:02,102
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

787
00:40:06,552 --> 00:40:08,472
♪Too much of shame♪

788
00:40:08,818 --> 00:40:11,614
♪To waste it crying♪

789
00:40:14,072 --> 00:40:15,992
♪Leave all behind you♪

790
00:40:15,992 --> 00:40:18,272
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

791
00:40:18,392 --> 00:40:20,621
♪You know how far you've gone♪

792
00:40:20,756 --> 00:40:23,032
♪In the fire you rise again♪

793
00:40:23,218 --> 00:40:25,578
♪You made it through the worst♪

794
00:40:25,716 --> 00:40:27,920
♪The best is yet to come♪

795
00:40:28,163 --> 00:40:30,303
♪The best is yet to come♪

796
00:40:33,005 --> 00:40:34,328
♪Isn't it magical♪

797
00:40:34,328 --> 00:40:35,960
♪Listen, look,
how beautiful the night is♪

798
00:40:35,992 --> 00:40:38,459
♪With countless lights on,
is someone heartbroken again♪

799
00:40:38,459 --> 00:40:40,912
♪The sound of a heart
shattering on the ground is so crisp♪

800
00:40:40,993 --> 00:40:43,641
♪Turn on a light.
A lonely heart needs comfort♪

801
00:40:43,730 --> 00:40:46,261
♪Sweat, toil, dawn, dusk♪

802
00:40:46,341 --> 00:40:48,563
♪Devaluing self-respect
just for some hot food♪

803
00:40:48,705 --> 00:40:49,786
♪But I don't want to♪

804
00:40:49,895 --> 00:40:52,161
♪Sell dignity at a price,
trampling on past vows♪

805
00:40:52,277 --> 00:40:53,342
♪Until 3 AM♪

806
00:40:53,513 --> 00:40:54,718
♪Locking dreams away in a drawer♪

807
00:40:54,872 --> 00:40:56,105
♪Just to earn some meager profit♪

808
00:40:56,196 --> 00:40:58,560
♪No matter how hard I try,
it only brings sobs♪

809
00:40:58,707 --> 00:41:03,117
♪Renewing yearly, gone with no return,
teetering, utterly bland♪

810
00:41:17,842 --> 00:41:19,278
♪Leave all behind you♪

811
00:41:19,382 --> 00:41:21,869
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

812
00:41:22,052 --> 00:41:24,181
♪You know how far you've gone♪

813
00:41:24,368 --> 00:41:26,708
♪In the fire you rise again♪

814
00:41:26,776 --> 00:41:29,042
♪You made it through the worst♪

815
